        "q": "Why would I need an alternative to the Strava API?",
        "a": "Strava is activity- and social-focused, so it models runs, rides, and segments but not full health metrics like sleep stages, HRV, resting heart rate, or recovery scores. It also has published rate limits, effectively one webhook subscription per application, and an athlete-permission (per-user OAuth) model. Teams that need device health data or higher volume usually add another source alongside Strava rather than replacing it."
